org.openntf.domino.nsfdata.structs.cd

Class CDACTIONBAR

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openntf.domino.nsfdata.structs.AbstractStruct
      • org.openntf.domino.nsfdata.structs.cd.CDRecord
        • org.openntf.domino.nsfdata.structs.cd.CDACTIONBAR
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class CDACTIONBAR
extends CDRecord
    The designer of a form or view may define custom actions for that form or view. The attributes for the button bar are stored in the CDACTIONBAR record in the $ACTIONS and/or $V5ACTIONS item for the design note describing the form or view. (actods.h)
    Since:
    Lotus Notes/Domino 4.5
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
